ModWorkshop API Documentation

Postman collection → OpenAPI spec →

Introduction

Base URL: http://192.168.146.128:8000

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Authenticating requests

This API is not authenticated.

Mods

GET mods/{mod_id}/download

GET
api.modworkshop.net
/mods/{mod_id}/download

Headers

Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

URL Parameters

mod_id
integer
required

The ID of the mod.

Example:
38825
Headers
:
:
URL Parameters
:
Request failed with error

Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network. If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS. You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Received response

Example request: 
curl --request GET \
    --get "api.modworkshop.net/mods/38825/download" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "api.modworkshop.net/mods/38825/download"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
Example response:

Mods

GET
api.modworkshop.net
/mods

Returns many mods, has a few options for searching the right mods

Headers

Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

query
string

Must not be greater than 150 characters.

Example:
rzbfmvedosglwpahmmet
limit
integer

Must be at least 1. Must not be greater than 50.

Example:
20
game_id
integer

Must be at least 1.

Example:
88
category_id
integer

Must be at least 1.

Example:
89
tags
integer[]

Must be at least 1.

Example:
[59]
liked
boolean
categories
integer[]

Must be at least 1.

Example:
[41]
block_tags
integer[]

Must be at least 1.

Example:
[10]
user_id
integer

Must be at least 1.

Example:
20
collab
boolean
ignore_blocked_users
boolean
Example:
1
sort
string

Must be one of bumped_at, published_at, likes, downloads, views, score, weekly_score, daily_score, random, or name.

Example:
views
Headers
:
:
Body
{ "query": "rzbfmvedosglwpahmmet", "limit": 20, "game_id": 88, "category_id": 89, "tags": [ 59 ], "liked": false, "categories": [ 41 ], "block_tags": [ 10 ], "user_id": 20, "collab": false, "ignore_blocked_users": true, "sort": "views" }
Request failed with error

Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network. If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS. You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Received response

Example request: 
curl --request GET \
    --get "api.modworkshop.net/mods" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"query\": \"rzbfmvedosglwpahmmet\",
    \"limit\": 20,
    \"game_id\": 88,
    \"category_id\": 89,
    \"tags\": [
        59
    ],
    \"liked\": false,
    \"categories\": [
        41
    ],
    \"block_tags\": [
        10
    ],
    \"user_id\": 20,
    \"collab\": false,
    \"ignore_blocked_users\": true,
    \"sort\": \"views\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "api.modworkshop.net/mods"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "query": "rzbfmvedosglwpahmmet",
    "limit": 20,
    "game_id": 88,
    "category_id": 89,
    "tags": [
        59
    ],
    "liked": false,
    "categories": [
        41
    ],
    "block_tags": [
        10
    ],
    "user_id": 20,
    "collab": false,
    "ignore_blocked_users": true,
    "sort": "views"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Example response:
Headers 
                                                            cache-control
                                                            : no-cache, private
                                                                                                                    content-type
                                                            : application/json
                                                                                                                    x-ratelimit-limit
                                                            : 60
                                                                                                                    x-ratelimit-remaining
                                                            : 53
                                                                                                                    vary
                                                            : Origin
                                                         
{
    "message": "The selected game id is invalid.",
    "errors": {
        "game_id": [
            "The selected game id is invalid."
        ]
    }
}

Get Mod

GET
api.modworkshop.net
/mods/{id}

Returns a single mod

Headers

Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

URL Parameters

id
integer
required

The ID of the mod.

Example:
38825
Headers
:
:
URL Parameters
:
Request failed with error

Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network. If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS. You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Received response

Example request: 
curl --request GET \
    --get "api.modworkshop.net/mods/38825" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"

);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

curl --request POST \

    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "api.modworkshop.net/mods/38825/comments"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
